  dummyurl =     "http://iopscience.iop.org/0022-3727/31/6/015",
  annote =	 "The {Levitron\textsuperscript{\texttrademark}} is an
                  axisymmetric top magnetized parallel to its symmetry
                  axis. It can levitate above a specially constructed magnetic
                  base if spun rapidly enough (and, as we found, not too
                  rapidly). We have written a complete, coupled,
                  nondissipative Hamiltonian system that describes the
                  dynamics of the top. The system is twelfth order and is too
                  complicated for general analysis. We have integrated the
                  equations of motion numerically and found a region of a
                  two-dimensional manifold of initial conditions for which
                  levitation persists. We find that the amplitude of the
                  dynamic variables in the region of persistent levitation
                  scales linearly with the initial tilt of the axis with
