  annote =	 "Stable levitation of one magnet by another with no energy
                  input is usually prohibited by Earnshaw's theorem. However,
                  the introduction of diamagnetic material at special
                  locations can stabilize such levitation. A magnet can even
                  be stably suspended between (diamagnetic) fingertips. A very
