                  about half the radius of the solenoid. The theory explains
                  recent experiments by \emph{Geim et al}, in which a variety
                  of objects (one of which was a living frog) was levitated in
                  a field of about 16~T. Similar ideas explain the stability
                  of a spinning magnet
                  {(Levitron\textsuperscript{\texttrademark})} above a
                  magnetized base plate. Stable levitation of paramagnets is
